Meet Magic Wanda, the happy young witch who just flew into the neighborhood! She and her friends are sure to enchant you with her wonderous adventures!

The Adventures of MAGIC WANDA and her Spellbinding Friends is an exciting tale about the power of friendship that also teaches valuable lessons. Wanda and her companions must stick together to overcome Nadia the Nasty, the meanest witch in the land. Among Wanda's magical friends are: a girl named Flexibel who desperately wants to learn to dance, a little league star named Sammy who has trouble in school, talented sculptor Ralphie -- plus a brainy squirrel, an absent-minded koala bear, and much more! Together, Wanda and her friends use love and kindness to help each other overcome difficulties, hardships, and of course mean old Nadia the Nasty!

This book is perfect for kids ages 5 through 10. All eleven chapters, written in rhyme, are accompanied by beautiful black and white illustrations.

"Even better than Isabella Castaspella!" raves children's book expert Colin Jacobs.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.
